<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">A Baffling Contradiction in U.S. Data <span class="divider"> | </span></span> The first quarter of this year was the worst for the United States economy since 2009, but employers hired more people than in any quarter over the last six years. It is hard to imagine how both of those statements could be true, but they are what government statistics indicate, Floyd Norris writes in the High &#038; Low Finance column.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/07/11/business/economy/in-us-data-a-contradiction-that-makes-no-sense.html"> NEW YORK TIMES </a></span></p>
